Qatar on Monday asked citizens to leave the United Arab Emirates within 14 days to comply with a decision by Abu Dhabi to sever ties with Doha, the Qatari embassy in Abu Dhabi said on social media.&#8220;Qatari citizens must leave the UAE within 14 days, in accordance with the statement issued by the concerned Emirati parties,&#8221; the embassy tweeted.Those who cannot travel directly to Doha should go through Kuwait or Oman, it said.-Reuters